INSERT INTO `lime_questions` VALUES (1344,0,263515,69,'O','platform_agreement_problems_reversed','Technology Platforms','Are you aware of any problems arising from the use of different technology platforms in supporting the collaboration (e.g., sharing information, communicating, etc.)? If so, please describe them.','','<p>\n	Note: In other words, how compatible do you think the different platforms will be? Will you be able to move information between them, as necessary, without time-consuming extra effort?</p>\n<p>\n	Examples of a \'technology platform\' include a computer operating system, instrument, equipment, design/development environment, etc. Different technology platforms support different kinds of collaborative work, for example, Google Apps may support synchronous document editing better than DropBox.</p>\n','N','N',76,'en',0,0,'',''),(1343,0,263515,69,'O','federation_plan','Data Sharing Plan','As far as you know, is there a documented plan for how to share data or code?','','Note: Such a plan might specify standard formats, who will have access to what data or code (and when), and how data or code will be made accessible to project members.','N','N',75,'en',0,0,'',''),(1342,0,263515,69,'M','tech_savvy','Collaboration Technologies','To the best of your knowledge, which technologies are being used in the project?  Below are technologies other collaborations have used.  Please check all that you know to be in regular use as part of the {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} collaboration.  If {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} is using a technology system not listed, please describe it in the \'other\' field below.','','','Y','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1341,0,263515,68,'O','knowledge_management_reversed','Knowledge Management ','As far as you are aware, is there an agreed-upon plan in place to keep track of documents, minutes of meetings, and any other records of project activities?','','Note: such a plan may be enacted formally or informally, and would consider who is responsible for managing documents and records, where they will be stored, and how they will be disseminated to project members.','N','N',10,'en',0,0,'',''),(1340,0,263515,68,'O','financial_considerations_reversed','Financial Considerations','As far as you are aware, are there any outstanding financial considerations to be resolved in the project?','','Note: examples of \'financial considerations\' include how money will be spent, who decides how it will be spent, how invoices are processed, how funds can be advanced, regulatory compliance, etc. Financial issues include anything that involves the allocation of funding within the project or the movement of funds between the project and external entities.','N','N',9,'en',0,0,'',''),(1337,0,263515,68,'O','communication_plan','Communication Plan','Does a communication plan exist for the project?','','Note: A communication plan is a formal or informal agreement about what technologies participants will use to share conversations and/or documents, how quickly people are expected to respond, etc.','N','N',6,'en',0,0,'',''),(1338,0,263515,68,'O','reflection_plan','Collective Reflection','To your knowledge, are there planned opportunities for collective reflection and redirection for the project?','','Note: a \'plan for reflection and redirection\' is a documented plan for project members to reflect regularly on the progress of the project and to discuss options for redirection of project activities to accomplish its goals. This can come, for example, in the form of an external advisory board and an annual meeting with the project leaders.','N','N',7,'en',0,0,'',''),(1339,0,263515,68,'O','legal_issues_reversed','Legal Issues','As far as you are aware, are there any outstanding legal issues to be resolved in the project?','','Note: examples of legal issues include issues of intellectual property, regulatory compliance, ownership of facilities, etc.','N','N',8,'en',0,0,'',''),(1335,0,263515,68,'O','designated_project_manager','Designated Project Manager','Is there a designated project manager for this project? ','','Note: A project manager is different than the principal investigator in roles, though they may be assigned to the same person. Principal investigators are typically the chief scientist inspiring the work and getting it funded. A project manager is the person responsible for assigning roles and responsibilities, keeping track of progress, lead decisions on redirection if necessary, etc.','N','N',4,'en',0,0,'',''),(1336,0,263515,68,'O','respected_project_manager','Respected Project Manager','Is the project manager someone respected by the team as far as you know?','','','N','N',5,'en',0,0,'',''),(1333,0,263515,68,'O','point_person','Point Person','Across the project, is there a \"point person\" at each site where {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} people are located? ','','Note: a point person is a primary point of contact at a site who can help you find the right people for a particular issue.','N','N',2,'en',0,0,'',''),(1334,0,263515,68,'O','management_plan','Management Plan','As far as you know, is there an agreed-upon management plan to coordinate among sites in this project? ','','Note: a \'management plan\' describes various roles, responsibilities, and activities by which a project\'s work is conducted.','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1330,0,263515,67,'O','community_efficacy_reversed','Overcome Obstacles','To what extent do you think the people in {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} have an attitude that they can overcome obstacles or challenges as they arise?','','','N','N',8,'en',0,0,'',''),(1331,0,263515,68,'O','adequate_time_reversed','Adequate Time','To what extent do you believe the leaders are devoting enough time to this project?','','','N','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1332,0,263515,68,'O','work_time_overlap_remotes_reversed','Time Zone Differences','To what extent have time zone differences between participants been a challenge for accomplishing your project work?','','','N','N',1,'en',0,0,'',''),(1329,0,263515,67,'O','goals_compatible_reversed','Compatible Goals','To what extent do you think the goals of the various project participants are compatible? ','','Note: \'compatible,\' here, means that people are working towards goals that do not conflict with each other. An example of incompatible goals from a past study was a project\'s computer scientists\' desire to rapidly develop experimental software prototypes (that may have bugs) vs. that project\'s research scientists\' need for production-quality software (without bugs).','N','N',7,'en',0,0,'',''),(1323,0,263515,67,'M','motivation','Motivation','What is your motivation to work together on this project? (Check all that apply.)','','','Y','N',1,'en',0,0,'',''),(1324,0,263515,67,'O','value','Fair Rewards','To what extent do you believe that there are fair rewards for people\'s efforts in {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316}? ','','Note: \'rewards\' can refer to anything that people seek as a result of their work, whether that\'s publications, recognition, a paycheck, or whatever. \'Fair\' refers to the extent of balance between effort and reward.','N','N',2,'en',0,0,'',''),(1325,0,263515,67,'O','trust_reliable_reversed','Reliability','In general, to what extent do you feel that your remote colleagues in {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} are reliable, i.e., that they both fulfill their commitments and do so on time?','','','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1326,0,263515,67,'O','high_quality','Contribution Quality','In general, what do you think is the quality level of the contributions from your remote colleagues?','','','N','N',4,'en',0,0,'',''),(1327,0,263515,67,'O','trust_best_interest_reversed','Best Interests','In general, to what extent do you trust that others in {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} keep your needs in mind and won\'t take advantage of you? ','','Note: An example of this would be a redistribution of resources without your needs in mind.','N','N',5,'en',0,0,'',''),(1328,0,263515,67,'O','trust_fair_distribution_reversed','Distribution of Resources','In general, to what extent do you trust there is a fair distribution of resources among {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} collaborators?','','Note: By \'fair,\' we don\'t necessarily mean \'equal,\' but appropriate to the different kinds of work different collaborators are doing for the project. ','N','N',6,'en',0,0,'',''),(1321,0,263515,66,'O','common_working_style','Common Working Style','To what extent do you think {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} team members share a common management/working style?','','<span id=\"internal-source-marker_0.3117913210996254\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">Note: \'Management/working style\' broadly refers to the ways in which the work is organized and in which decisions are made.</span>','N','N',4,'en',0,0,'',''),(1320,0,263515,66,'O','helpful_culture','Helpfulness','To what extent do you think the people in {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} actively help each other?','','','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1319,0,263515,66,'O','thesaurus','Terminology Documents','Are there documents explaining the terminology, procedures, or policies in use so that {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} members are able to understand each other?','','','N','N',2,'en',0,0,'',''),(1314,0,263515,65,'Q','demographics','Demographics','','','','N','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1315,0,263515,65,'Q','project_detail','Project Details','','','','N','N',9,'en',0,0,'',''),(1316,0,263515,65,'L','project_name','','Project you are referring to in your answers:','','','N','N',1,'en',0,0,'',''),(1317,0,263515,66,'O','first_time','First Time','When {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316} started, was it the first time most of the people were working with each other?','','','N','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1318,0,263515,66,'O','common_tongue','Common Tongue','In {INSERTANS:263515X65X1316}, to what extent do you think mo