l actively help each other to resolve issues as they arise?','','','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1045,0,59461,52,'O','common_working_style','Common Working Style','To what extent do you think {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} project members will share a common management/working style?','','<span id=\"internal-source-marker_0.3117913210996254\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;\">Note: \'Management/working style\' broadly refers to the ways in which the work is organized and by which decisions are made.</span>','N','N',4,'en',0,0,'',''),(1046,0,59461,53,'O','collaboration_culture','Naturally Collaborative','To what extent do you think the anticipated project members will be naturally collaborative?','','Note: some kinds of work are naturally collaborative (e.g., freely sharing information, pro-actively helpful, etc.), and some kinds are naturally competitive, vying for the same goals or resources (e.g., funding, publications, a Nobel Prize, etc.). Neither is inherently good nor bad, but understanding this can inform decisions about how to organize the work.','N','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1047,0,59461,53,'M','motivation','Motivation','What are your motivations to work together on this project? (Check all that apply.)','','','Y','N',1,'en',0,0,'',''),(1048,0,59461,53,'O','value','Fair Rewards','To what extent do you believe that there will be fair rewards for people\'s efforts in {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040}? ','','Note: \'rewards\' can refer to anything that people seek as a result of their work, whether that\'s publications, recognition, a paycheck, or whatever. \'Fair\' refers to the extent of balance between effort and reward.','N','N',2,'en',0,0,'',''),(1049,0,59461,53,'O','trust_reliable_reversed','Reliability','In general, to what extent do you feel that your remote colleagues in {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} will be reliable, i.e., that they both fulfill their commitments and do so on time?','','','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1050,0,59461,53,'O','high_quality','Contribution Quality','In general, what do you think will be the quality level of the contributions from your remote colleagues?','','','N','N',4,'en',0,0,'',''),(1051,0,59461,53,'O','trust_best_interest_reversed','Best Interests','In general, to what extent do you trust that others in {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} will keep your needs in mind and won\'t take advantage of you? ','','Note: An example of this would be a redistribution of resources without consideration of your needs or plans.','N','N',5,'en',0,0,'',''),(1052,0,59461,53,'O','trust_fair_distribution_reversed','Distribution of Resources','In general, to what extent do you trust there will be a fair distribution of resources among {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} collaborators?','','Note: By \'fair,\' we don\'t necessarily mean \'equal,\' but a distribution appropriate to the different kinds of work people are doing for the project. ','N','N',6,'en',0,0,'',''),(1053,0,59461,53,'O','goals_compatible_reversed','Compatible Goals','To what extent do you think the goals of the anticipated project participants will be compatible? ','','Note: \'compatible,\' here, means that people are working towards goals that do not conflict with each other. An example of incompatible goals, from a past study, was a project\'s computer scientists\' desire to rapidly develop experimental software prototypes (that may have bugs) vs. that project\'s research scientists\' need for production-quality software (without bugs).','N','N',7,'en',0,0,'',''),(1054,0,59461,53,'O','community_efficacy_reversed','Overcome Obstacles','To what extent do you think the people in {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} will have an attitude that they can overcome obstacles or challenges as they arise?','','','N','N',8,'en',0,0,'',''),(1055,0,59461,54,'O','adequate_time_reversed','Adequate Time','To what extent do you believe project leaders will be able to devote enough time to this project?','','','N','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1056,0,59461,54,'O','work_time_overlap_remotes_reversed','Time Zone Differences','To what extent do you expect time zone differences between participants will be a challenge for accomplishing your project work?','','','N','N',1,'en',0,0,'',''),(1057,0,59461,54,'O','point_person','Point Person','Across the project, will there be a designated \"point person\" at each site where more than one {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} person will be located? ','','Note: a point person is a primary point of contact at a site who can help you find the right people to address a particular issue.','N','N',2,'en',0,0,'',''),(1058,0,59461,54,'O','management_plan','Management Plan','As far as you know, will there be an agreed-upon management plan in place (to coordinate among sites in this project) when the project starts? ','','Note: a \'management plan\' describes various roles, responsibilities, and activities by which a project\'s work is conducted.','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1059,0,59461,54,'O','designated_project_manager','Designated Project Manager','Will there be a project manager designated for this project? ','','Note: A project manager is different than the principal investigator in roles, though they may be assigned to the same person. Principal investigators are typically the chief scientist inspiring the work and getting it funded. A project manager is the person responsible for assigning roles and responsibilities, keeping track of progress, leading decisions on redirection if necessary, etc.','N','N',4,'en',0,0,'',''),(1060,0,59461,54,'O','respected_project_manager','Respected Project Manager','Is the project manager someone respected by the team as far as you know?','','','N','N',5,'en',0,0,'',''),(1061,0,59461,54,'O','communication_plan','Communication Plan','Will a communication plan exist for the project?','','Note: A communication plan is a formal or informal agreement about what technologies participants will use to share conversations and/or documents, how quickly people are expected to respond, etc.','N','N',6,'en',0,0,'',''),(1062,0,59461,54,'O','reflection_plan','Collective Reflection','To your knowledge, will there be planned opportunities for collective reflection and possible redirection for the project?','','Note: a \'plan for reflection and redirection\' is a documented plan for project members to reflect regularly on the progress of the project and to discuss options for redirection of project activities to accomplish its goals. This can come, for example, in the form of an external advisory board or an annual meeting with the project leaders.','N','N',7,'en',0,0,'',''),(1063,0,59461,54,'O','legal_issues_reversed','Legal Issues','As far as you are aware, are there any outstanding legal issues to be resolved before the project begins?','','Note: examples of legal issues include issues of intellectual property, regulatory compliance, ownership of facilities, etc.','N','N',8,'en',0,0,'',''),(1064,0,59461,54,'O','financial_considerations_reversed','Financial Considerations','Assuming your {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} proposal is funded, are there any other financial considerations to be resolved before the project begins?','','Note: examples of \'financial considerations\' include how money will be spent, who decides how it will be spent, how invoices are processed, how funds can be advanced, regulatory compliance, etc. Financial issues include anything that involves the allocation of funding within the project or the movement of funds between the project and external entities.','N','N',9,'en',0,0,'',''),(1065,0,59461,54,'O','knowledge_management_reversed','Knowledge Management ','As far as you are aware, will there be an agreed-upon plan in place to keep track of documents, minutes of meetings, and any other records of project activities?','','Note: such a plan may be enacted formally or informally, and would consider who is responsible for managing documents and records, where they will be stored, file naming conventions, how they will be disseminated to project members, etc.','N','N',10,'en',0,0,'',''),(1066,0,59461,55,'M','tech_savvy','Collaboration Technologies','To the best of your knowledge, which technologies will be used to support collaboration in the project?  Below are technologies other collaborations have used.  Please check all that you expect to be in regular use as part of the {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} collaboration.  If {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} will be using any technology system not listed, please describe in the \'other\' field below.','','','Y','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1067,0,59461,55,'O','federation_plan','Data Sharing Plan','As far as you know, will there be a documented plan for how data will be shared among project members?','','Note: Such a plan might specify standard formats, who will have access to what data (and when), and how data will be made accessible to project members.','N','N',75,'en',0,0,'',''),(1068,0,59461,55,'O','platform_agreement_problems_reversed','Technology Platforms','Do you foresee any problems arising from the use of different technology platforms in supporting the collaboration (e.g., sharing information, communicating, etc.)? If so, please describe them.','','<p>\n	Note: In other words, how compatible do you think the different platforms will be? Will you be able to move information or materials between them, as necessary, without time-consuming extra effort?</p>\n<p>\n	Examples of a \'technology platform\' include a computer operating system, instrument, equipment, design/development environment, etc. Different technology platforms support different kinds of collaborative work.</p>\n','N','N',76,'en',0,0,'',''),(1069,0,59461,55,'O','networking_support_reversed','Computer Network','How well do you think the computer networking infrastructure, at each site, will support both the work and communication needs of {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} participants?','','Note: A good computer networking infrastructure will provide reliable Internet connectivity and sufficient bandwidth to support your online activities.','N','N',77,'en',0,0,'',''),(1070,0,59461,55,'O','tech_support','Tech Support','As far as you know, will there be sufficient technical support at each site where the project collaborators are located?','','Note: \'technical support\' refers to trained personnel with sufficient resources (including time) to resolve technical problems with minimal delay.','N','N',78,'en',0,0,'',''),(1071,0,59461,55,'O','certifying_new_users','Instrument Training','If your project involves people using an instrument remotely (like an observatory or environmental sensor), will there be a plan for training and certifying users in its operation?','','','N','N',80,'en',0,0,'',''),(1072,0,59461,56,'O','predicted_success','Predicted Success','In your opinion, will this project be successful? Please explain your answer in the box below and include a description of things you would consider to be \'signs of success\' for the project over the foreseeable future.','','Note:  \"Signs of success\" and \"foreseeable\" are understandably subjective, and your response might vary with different periods of time. We encourage you to respond from your personal perspective and to consider what might constitute short-, intermediate-, and long- term successes.','N','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1073,0,59461,56,'Y','identify_role','Identify Your Role','Thank you for participating. Having answered these questions, do you feel you are comfortable about us identifying you by your role in publications about the Wizard?','','You described your role as: <em>{INSERTANS:59461X51X1039prole}</em>','N','N',1,'en',0,0,'',''),(1074,0,59461,56,'Y','identify_project','Identify the Project','Do you feel comfortable about us identifying {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040} in publications about the Wizard?','','','N','N',2,'en',0,0,'',''),(1075,0,59461,56,'T','final_comments','Submit the Survey','<p>\n	When you hit the \"submit\" button below, you will be provided with a report of the overall strengths and vulnerabilities of your project, according to the responses you indicated. If you would like further information about any of it, please feel free to contact us:<br />\n	<br />\n	Gary Olson (<a href=\"mailto:gary.olson@uci.edu\">gary.olson@uci.edu</a>)</p>\n<p>\n	 </p>\n<p>\n	If you can think of anything we did not ask but should know about, or you have any comments about this experience, please enter them in the box below.<br />\n	 </p>\n','','','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1076,0,59461,57,'T','type_of_work','Type of Work','First of all, please describe the type of work you expect to do in {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040}. Two or three sentences are sufficient, but feel free to say as much as you wish.','','','N','N',0,'en',0,0,'',''),(1077,0,59461,57,'O','interdependent','Interdependence','How dependent do you think you and your remote colleagues will be on each other to get the work done? ','','Note: We include both task dependency and coordination dependency here. Task dependency means that parts of one person\'s work are dependent on the completion of parts of another\'s work. Coordination dependency means that people must jointly make decisions as tasks progress.   ','N','N',2,'en',0,0,'',''),(1078,0,59461,57,'O','ambiguous_reversed','Routine','In general, for {INSERTANS:59461X51X1040}, how routine do you expect the work with your remote colleagues to be?','','Note: To clarify, is the work you will do with your remote colleagues straightforward and are the tasks well understood? In other words, do you and your colleagues have a good sense of what will need to be done and how each person will contribute to the work? Or will it be an ongoing process of figuring out how to do the work, who needs to contribute, and who will be responsible for each task?','N','N',3,'en',0,0,'',''),(1079,0,59461,55,'O','user_centered_design','User-Centere